PrecisEnactment of the PROVINCIAL EMERGENCIES FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE ORDER NO. 23 - which declares a provincial emergency, namely the severe rainstorm and flooding which occurred in southern British Columbia between March 18 and March 24, 1997, to be of concern to the federal government, and authorizes the provision of financial assistance in respect thereof.
